<h5 class="text-dark">Designed for those who want to conduct content audits and analyses.</h5>
<p class="mb-3 text-dark">
    <span class="fw-semibold">Check Yourself</span> is designed for researchers, students, activists, journalists, and anyone else who want to conduct content audits and analyses. Since it originated from a project that aimed to challenge harmful stereotypes, it can also be helpful for writers who want to proactively check their writing for biases or, in other words, "check themselves." If you believe the tool could benefit your research or media accountability project, please reach out. We are enthusiastic about supporting spin-off and integration efforts, especially for community-led projects that address the role of journalism in perpetuating harmful biases and representation.
</p>

